<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<RelativeLayout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="100dp"
    android:orientation="vertical"
    android:id="@+id/custom_list_view_item">

    <ImageButton
        android:id="@+id/btnSoulType"
        android:layout_width="100dp"
        android:layout_height="match_parent"
        android:layout_alignParentStart="true"/>
    <TextView
        android:id="@+id/tvSender"
        android:layout_width="125dp"
        android:layout_height="match_parent"
        android:text="Testing"
        android:textSize="30sp"
        android:layout_toEndOf="@+id/btnSoulType"/>
    <TextView
        android:id="@+id/tvSoulLength"
        android:layout_width="50dp"
        android:layout_height="match_parent"
        android:text="0:20"
        android:textAlignment="center"
        android:layout_toEndOf="@+id/tvSender"
        android:textSize="25sp" />
    <ImageButton
        android:id="@+id/btnExpandDetails"
        android:layout_alignParentEnd="true"
        android:layout_width="100dp"
        android:layout_height="match_parent" />
    <!--Will need:
    Sender Name/ID (String - userid, maybe color/flair)
    Location (x meters away, 'north'
    Message length (String, 'x:xx seconds')
    Content Type? (Image)
    Report button? (Swipe in, then button click - will be the hardest part)
    Ignore button? (Swipe to remove?)
    (Play Button is the selectable listview item itself)

    In order to include all of this elegantly, we will need a button to allow each message to expand on its own.
    The default view should include the sender, message length and the content type.  Other functionality should be within the expandable view.
    -->
</RelativeLayout>